1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,459
-Hi!
-Oh!

2
00:00:01,459 --> 00:00:04,800
-Oh, no. No.

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:06,343
-Hello.

4
00:00:06,343 --> 00:00:09,462
"Haircut" started based
on a real event in my life

5
00:00:09,462 --> 00:00:14,153
where I shaved my head
and I found myself saying,
"I like it."

6
00:00:17,898 --> 00:00:20,067
I was lying.
So I wrote it as a sketch

7
00:00:20,067 --> 00:00:21,862
at the Groundlings,
and it went for years.

8
00:00:21,862 --> 00:00:24,963
It was directed
by Deanna Oliver first,
and then Bob Odenkirk.

9
00:00:24,963 --> 00:00:28,448
I beat that thing to death.
I did it -- I did it everywhere.

10
00:00:28,448 --> 00:00:32,014
This is a woman who is
insecure about her new haircut.

11
00:00:32,014 --> 00:00:35,344
I brought it in as an Update and
we had the wig and everything.

12
00:00:35,344 --> 00:00:37,418
It was this huge spiky wig.

13
00:00:37,418 --> 00:00:40,560
Not many people
could pull this off, but I can.

14
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:44,025
Someone must have saw it
and said,
"That's not
going to happen here."

15
00:00:44,025 --> 00:00:48,147
And it got cut 20 minutes
before the dress show.

16
00:00:48,147 --> 00:00:52,423
Then I was asked to bring
it back with a different wig
and it got cut after dress.

17
00:00:52,423 --> 00:00:55,400
I think we may have tried
it three weeks in a row.

18
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:57,369
I look crazy.

19
00:00:57,369 --> 00:01:01,197
But thank God it happened
because it's meant
to be a sketch

20
00:01:01,197 --> 00:01:03,679
and they helped me see that.

21
00:01:03,679 --> 00:01:05,887
-I hate it!

22
00:01:05,887 --> 00:01:09,761
-Even though it didn't go on TV,
the whole staff would quote it,

23
00:01:09,761 --> 00:01:11,076
and people would go,
"I like it."

24
00:01:11,076 --> 00:01:11,841
-I like it.

25
00:01:11,841 --> 00:01:14,191
-And I feel like
the character was just so big

26
00:01:14,191 --> 00:01:17,987
it needed to be surrounded by a
bunch of people staring at her.

27
00:01:17,987 --> 00:01:20,727
It was a real journey
with the look of the hair.

28
00:01:20,727 --> 00:01:23,762
-The hair.
-The hair.
-The hair.
-The hair.

29
00:01:23,762 --> 00:01:26,252
-They originally wanted
it to be a bob,

30
00:01:26,252 --> 00:01:29,465
and I had just had
a design meeting

31
00:01:29,465 --> 00:01:33,404
with a whole 'nother sketch
of 5,000 bobs,

32
00:01:33,404 --> 00:01:35,893
and I was like,
"Well, that's not gonna work."

33
00:01:35,893 --> 00:01:39,974
The wig cannot be
the whole joke.
It had to be a build up.

34
00:01:39,974 --> 00:01:42,727
Like, why does she look
a little off?

35
00:01:42,727 --> 00:01:46,555
-We knew we wanted to, like,
turn and have her
reveal something.

36
00:01:46,555 --> 00:01:47,967
-So there was a skin square.

37
00:01:47,967 --> 00:01:51,640
I could only give this one
one shot at it

38
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,542
because we only had one go.

39
00:01:53,542 --> 00:01:55,320
-The skin square.

40
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:57,070
-Glen is such a great
straight man.

41
00:01:57,070 --> 00:02:00,709
He was so down
to let other people shine

42
00:02:00,709 --> 00:02:02,256
and he was so good
at supporting them.

43
00:02:02,256 --> 00:02:04,842
-And sometimes
when you write something
that a host is
a straighter part,

44
00:02:04,842 --> 00:02:07,201
you wonder,
are they going to be
excited to do this?

45
00:02:07,201 --> 00:02:10,703
When we were picking sketches,
he was like, "Oh, I love that.
Yeah, we have to do that."

46
00:02:10,703 --> 00:02:14,237
-Well, Melissa,
I really like it.

47
00:02:14,237 --> 00:02:15,917
-Me, too.

48
00:02:15,917 --> 00:02:19,931
-And with that, we are finished
with the interview.

49
00:02:21,019 --> 00:02:22,604
-Thank you so much.

50
00:02:22,604 --> 00:02:24,047
-I like it.

